    "response": "To compute the **sample standard deviation** of the data set:\n\n$$\n\\{25, 10, 0, 9, -1, -14, -21\\}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 1: Find the mean (average)\n\n$$\n\\text{Mean} = \\frac{25 + 10 + 0 + 9 + (-1) + (-14) + (-21)}{7}\n$$\n\n$$\n= \\frac{25 + 10 + 0 + 9 - 1 - 14 - 21}{7} = \\frac{18}{7}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 2: Compute the squared differences from the mean\n\n$$\n\\begin{align*}\n(25 - \\frac{18}{7})^2 &= \\left(\\frac{175 - 18}{7}\\right)^2 = \\left(\\frac{157}{7}\\right)^2 = \\frac{24649}{49} \\\\\n(10 - \\frac{18}{7})^2 &= \\left(\\frac{70 - 18}{7}\\right)^2 = \\left(\\frac{52}{7}\\right)^2 = \\frac{2704}{49} \\\\\n(0 - \\frac{18}{7})^2 &= \\left(-\\frac{18}{7}\\right)^2 = \\frac{324}{49} \\\\\n(9 - \\frac{18}{7})^2 &= \\left(\\frac{63 - 18}{7}\\right)^2 = \\left(\\frac{45}{7}\\right)^2 = \\frac{2025}{49} \\\\\n(-1 - \\frac{18}{7})^2 &= \\left(-\\frac{25}{7}\\right)^2 = \\frac{625}{49} \\\\\n(-14 - \\frac{18}{7})^2 &= \\left(-\\frac{104}{7}\\right)^2 = \\frac{10816}{49} \\\\\n(-21 - \\frac{18}{7})^2 &= \\left(-\\frac{153}{7}\\right)^2 = \\frac{23409}{49} \\\\\n\\end"
